SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1280
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to provide for the adjournment sine die of the
One Hundred Fourteenth General Assembly.
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that the One Hundred Fourteenth General Assembly
stand in adjournment sine die at the close of business in both houses on Thursday, April 23,
2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that any standing, special, select, or ad hoc committee of
the General Assembly may meet after adjournment for the purpose of considering or
investigating any matter of State business within the scope of the committee's authority and
direct any necessary reports to the next General Assembly or any committee of the next
General Assembly.
